# one-resume — locations of the sibling repos this pipeline reads from / writes to.
#
# Copy to `.env` to override. EVERY var is OPTIONAL: when unset, the defaults
# below assume the standard side-by-side layout (all repos under one parent dir):
#
#   <parent>/one-resume          ← this repo
#   <parent>/pro-profile-source  ← markdown content        (CONTENT_DIR)
#   <parent>/pro-landing         ← the website             (SITE_PUBLIC_CV_DIR, SITE_LOCALES_DIR)
#
# Values may be absolute or relative to your shell's working directory.

# Markdown sources. cv/, projects/, freelance/, and special/ live directly
# under this directory.
# Default: ../pro-profile-source
# CONTENT_DIR=

# Where the 4 public PDFs (en.pdf, it.pdf, projects.pdf, progetti.pdf) are
# written — the site commits and ships these. Used by `pdf:public`.
# Default: ../pro-landing/public/cv
# SITE_PUBLIC_CV_DIR=

# Where the generated content JSON (en/content.json, it/content.json) is written.
# Used by `sync-locales`.
# Default: ../pro-landing/src/lib/locales
# SITE_LOCALES_DIR=

# Base dir for PRIVATE outputs (printed/pdf, printed/ats) — derived/freelance/
# special PDFs and all ATS DOCX. Not committed to the site.
# Default: ./printed (inside this repo)
# OUTPUT_DIR=
